JavaScript Cheat Sheet

Data types:
string -- "this is a s string." (needs quotations around them)
number -- 0-9 -- integers and floats can be used 
boolean -- 0 (false)/1 (true)
array -- ways of storing groups of information -- can put any of the other data types in it  (needs brackets around them with a semicolon to end it)

Variable (var):
a dynamic container that contains data
'x' stores a value for you - dynamic 


Function:
a block of code that can be executed at any time

Logic:
If/else

